[To find Tulcea, go to: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tulcea and
http://www.fallingrain.com/world/RO/37/Tulcea.html.

Anthrax is sporadic in Romania and is reported in the lower altitude
riverine regions. Latterly, they have reported 1-6 outbreaks each year
in cattle and infrequently in sheep, but in 2009, there was an
outbreak in some pigs in Tulcea, with 3 dead. The low level but
consistent reporting of human cases indicates that the disease in
livestock is largely going unreported. - Mod.MHJ]
